L-MODU(Low Molecular weight and Low Modulus polypropylen)




The low melting point of our L-Modu, short for low molecular weight and low modulus PP, along with its range viscosities make thsi advanced polyolefin an ideal choice for hot-melt adhesives, non-woeven fabrics, resin modifiers, elastic and pigment-dispersing agents..
See More











Crystalline Polymer (sPS) Xarec




Central Laboratory of Idemistu Kosan Co. Succeeded in the development of crystalline polymer (sPS) in 1985 from styrene monomer using a metallocene catalyst for the first time in the world. Based on this discovery, Idemitsu Petrochemical Co.
See More











